00:58:44,640 --> 00:58:50,800
Yes. Something that's worked really, really 
well for us is we think of product management  

727
00:58:51,720 --> 00:58:56,840
as partially like a go-to-market discipline 
in the same way that sales and marketing are,  

728
00:58:56,840 --> 00:59:00,200
right? When you talk to people and like, 
"Hey, tell me how product management works  

729
00:59:00,200 --> 00:59:02,040
in your company," they'll probably 
say something about like, "Well,  

730
00:59:02,040 --> 00:59:06,920
there's engineering product and design. They work 
in this triad, and here's how they interact and  

731
00:59:06,920 --> 00:59:14,600
collaborate," and we all understand why that's 
useful, why that's helpful, but this other form  

732
00:59:14,600 --> 00:59:18,280
of collaboration between product management, 
sales and marketing, I think it's something  

733
00:59:18,280 --> 00:59:26,920
that's probably really underexamined 
and often I feel like in organizations,  

734
00:59:26,920 --> 00:59:31,680
